Finding out what’s in your water and which water filter you need isn’t always straightforward. You need to find out which, if any, contaminants are in your tap water, and which filter works best for your situation. Plus, advice can vary depending on whether you’re on municipal or well water, and whether you have young children at home. This interactive will help you navigate the issues, especially related to three of the most concerning contaminants: lead, arsenic, and PFAS. ***